We recommended to the management to perform the following:
Require the Inventory and Disposal Committee to hasten the inspection, appraisal and disposal of those identified unserviceable heavy equipment and other motor vehicles owned by the LGU-Baungon, strictly adhering with the disposal procedures of the above-mentioned applicable rules and regulations;
Submit immediately to the audit team for auditorial review the complete documentary requirements prior review and inspection by the COA Regional Office No. 10’s Regional Technical Audit Group (RTAG);
Resort to proper disposition thru public auction or to other mode of disposal, if deemed appropriate, subject to applicable rules and regulations;
Require the Municipal Accountant to drop from the books of accounts those properties already disposed thru a drawing of Journal Entry Voucher, to be substantiated with complete documentation subject for post-audit; and,
Treat any proceeds from sale of unserviceable properties as a general income under the General Fund subject for supplemental appropriation to finance priority programs and projects of the municipality.

